t delicious and fatty fruits, the creation of beer, and our own sociality. Along the way, you will learn about the taste receptors you didn't even know you had, the best way to ferment a mastodon, the relationship between Paleolithic art and cheese, and much more.Blending irresistible storytelling with the latest science, Delicious is a deep history of flavor that will transform the way you think about human evolution and the gustatory pleasures of the foods we eat.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aFlavor. 0aPerceptionxPhysiological aspects. 0aSmellxPhysiological aspects. 0aTastexPhysiological aspects. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Evolution.2bisacsh  aAlice Waters.  aAnthony Bourdain.  aCatching Fire.  aChez Panisse.  aCooked.  aGulp.  aJacques Pepin.  aKitchen Confidential.  aMark Kurlansky.  aMary Roach.  aMichael Pollan.  aPeter Mayle.  aRichard Wrangham.  aSalt, Fat, Acid, Heat.  aSalt.  aSamin Nosrat.  aaroma.  abooks about cooking.  abooks about food.  acookbooks.  acooking.  aculinary books.  afarm to table.  afermentation.  afood books.  afood lovers.  aherbs.  ahistory of food.  akitchen.  ameat.  amouthfeel.  anatural history.  anutrition.  apaleo.  apleasure.  apopular science.  arecipes.  arestaurant guides.  awine.1 aSanchez, Monica, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2021 Englishz978311075414808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2021z9783110753912oZDB